# NestJS module / controller conventions

A feature module under `apps/<app>/src/modules/<feature>/` wires controllers and
delegates to domain/platform services. Generate skeletons with
`scripts/create-module.ts`.

## Controllers

- **Call services only.** No `@InjectRepository`, no `getRepository`, no
  `@nestjs/typeorm` in apps. If the operation is missing, add a method to the
  domain service and export it from the lib barrel, then call it.
- **Return a VO or `void`** â€” never an entity. Entityâ†’VO mapping happens in the
  lib's `mapper`/`assembler` (enforced by `no-entity-response`).
- **No business logic.** Orchestration lives in services; composition of multiple
  sources lives in assemblers; input validation lives in DTOs.
- **Delegate to an app application service; no multi-service orchestration or
  business branching in controllers.** If a handler touches more than one lib
  service or applies a business rule (status checks, token issuance, session
  rotation, security-event recordingâ€¦), move that into
  `apps/<app>/src/modules/<feature>/<feature>.service.ts` (an `@Injectable()`
  registered in the module `providers`) and have the controller call ONE method.
  The app service composes lib services and never injects a repository / imports
  another app. **HTTP transport (cookies / `@Res` / redirects) stays in the
  controller**; the app service returns plain data. A pure single-call delegation
  (controller â†’ one domain method â†’ VO) needs no app service.
- Annotate responses with `@ApiBaseResponse(Vo)` / `@ApiArrayResponse(Vo)` /
  `@ApiPaginatedResponse(Vo)` / `@ApiSuccessResponse()` from `@core/common`.
- Apply cross-cutting decorators: `@Public()` to open a route, `@Permissions(...)`
  on admin routes, `@OperationLogDecorator(...)` on writes, `@RateLimit(...)` on
  login/register/refresh/sso/password, `@CurrentUser()` / `@CurrentAdminUser()`
  to read the principal.

## DTOs and VOs

- DTOs are class-validator inputs (`create-user.dto.ts` â†’ `CreateUserDto`).
- VOs are outputs with `@ApiProperty` (`user.vo.ts` â†’ `UserVo`).
- Don't expose entities directly; build VOs.

## Modules

- Import the relevant lib module (e.g. `IdentityModule` from `@domains/identity`)
  and inject its services.
- Bind ports the app must provide (e.g. `ACCESS_CHECKER` â†’ access-control impl).

The `TransformInterceptor` wraps every returned VO in the unified envelope; never
build the envelope or call `res.send` from a controller.
